subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology. Named for the late Park Gyeong Ri (
1926–2008
), a great Korean writer who lived near Mt. Chiak.

Other 
morrisi
group species were reported in Beddard (1892, 1895, 
1896
), Chen (1933, 1936, 1938, 1946), Gates (1926, 1936, 
1968
), Michaelsen (1892, 1923, 
1927
), and Rosa (
1894
) recorded some species in 
morrisi
group, but all these earthworms species had different genital markings and male pore shapes.
